trans-unit.source: Some patterns may capture parts of the input that was used to compute the full match. This is the number of captured groups, which is also the maximal allowed argument to the group method.
trans-unit.target: 一些模式可能会捕获用于计算完全匹配的输入部分。这是捕获的组数，也是组方法允许的最大参数。

trans-unit.source: Some patterns, regular expressions in particular, may record substrings that were part of the matching. These are called groups in the Match object. Some patterns may never have any groups, and their matches always have zero groupCount.
trans-unit.target: 某些模式（尤其是正则表达式）可能会记录匹配中包含的子字符串。这些在Match对象中称为组。某些模式可能永远不会有任何组，并且它们的匹配项始终具有零groupCount。

trans-unit.source: Some types of iterable may have a different equality used for its elements. For example, a Set may have a custom equality (see Set.identity) that its contains uses. Likewise the Iterable returned by a Map.keys call should use the same equality that the Map uses for keys.
trans-unit.target: 某些类型的iterable可能具有用于其元素的不同相等性。例如，一个Set可能具有其 contains 用途的自定义等式（请参见Set.identity）。同样，由Map.keys调用返回的 Iterable 应该使用与 Map 用于键相同的相等性。

trans-unit.source: Sometimes the documentation refers to serializable objects. An object is serializable across isolates if and only if it is an instance of num, bool, String, a list of objects that are serializable across isolates, or a map with keys and values that are all serializable across isolates.
trans-unit.target: 有时文档提到可序列化的对象。当且仅当对象是num，bool，String的实例，可在各个隔离对象之间序列化的对象列表或带有键和值的映射都可在各个隔离对象之间序列化的对象时，该对象才可在隔离对象之间进行序列化。
